<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>SaaS Architecture Analysis - 2026-03-10</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f5f7fb;
      --panel: #ffffff;
      --text: #13233a;
      --muted: #4f627d;
      --line: #d9e2ef;
      --accent: #0f4c81;
    }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .wrap {
      max-width: 1100px;
      margin: 24px auto;
      padding: 0 16px 32px;
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);
    }
    h1, h2, h3 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    h2 { font-size: 22px; margin-top: 20px; }
    h3 { font-size: 18px; margin-top: 14px; }
    ul, ol { margin: 8px 0 8px 22px; }
    code { background: #eef3fa; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 6px; }
    .muted { color: var(--muted); }
    .mermaid {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 12px;
      background: #fff;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <h1>HRM_IlhaanSq SaaS - Architecture Analysis</h1>
      <p class="muted">Generated on 2026-03-10</p>
      <p>This file contains your full structured analysis plus rendered diagrams.</p>
      <p>Word-friendly text copy is available at: <code>docs/SaaS_Architecture_Analysis_2026-03-10.doc</code></p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>1. Project Overview</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Multi-tenant SaaS inventory/sales platform with tenant and super-admin experiences.</li>
        <li>Frontend stack: Next.js shell + React app + TanStack Query + Supabase client SDK.</li>
        <li>Backend stack: NestJS API for platform endpoints + Supabase Edge Functions for serverless flows.</li>
        <li>Persistence: Supabase Postgres with migrations and RLS-oriented schema evolution.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Evidence refs:</strong> <code>src/App.tsx#L103</code>, <code>src/views/SuperAdminDashboard.tsx#L121</code>, <code>apps/api/src/modules/platform-super-admin/platform-super-admin.controller.ts#L8</code></p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>2. Code Flow Analysis</h2>
      <p><strong>Entry points:</strong> <code>app/layout.tsx</code>, <code>app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx</code>, <code>src/next/LegacyAppClient.tsx</code>, <code>src/App.tsx</code>, <code>apps/api/src/main.ts</code></p>
      <p>Core flow: Next catch-all -> Legacy client mount -> Provider composition -> Protected routing -> Super-admin view -> Protected API calls -> Nest guard chain -> Service -> DB query -> UI render.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>3. Data Flow Analysis</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Data enters via UI forms, Nest API endpoints, Edge functions, and Stripe webhooks.</li>
        <li>Validation occurs in UI checks, Nest ValidationPipe, guards, and Edge function sanitizers.</li>
        <li>Data persists in Supabase Postgres; local browser state persists in cookies/localStorage as needed.</li>
        <li>Data exits via API JSON responses, OTP notifications, and external provider API calls.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>4. Project Lifecycle</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Startup orchestration: <code>scripts/dev-server.mjs</code> + env loading from <code>scripts/dev-env.mjs</code>.</li>
        <li>Runtime request chain includes Next middleware and client-side ProtectedRoute checks.</li>
        <li>Error handling includes React ErrorBoundary, API helper connectivity mapping, and service-level 503 mapping.</li>
        <li>Deployment pipeline includes PR gate, build, VPS release, PM2 reload, health checks, and rollback.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>5. Integration Points and Extension Hooks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>UI seams: route table in <code>src/App.tsx</code>, nav maps in <code>src/components/AppSidebar.tsx</code>.</li>
        <li>API seams: modular Nest controller/service files + <code>AppModule</code> registration.</li>
        <li>Serverless seams: one function per folder under <code>supabase/functions</code> with shared helpers in <code>_shared</code>.</li>
        <li>Schema seams: migration files in <code>supabase/migrations</code>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>6. New Module Fit</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>UI: add <code>src/views/&lt;Feature&gt;.tsx</code> + route + permissions + sidebar link.</li>
        <li>API: add <code>apps/api/src/modules/&lt;feature&gt;</code> and wire in <code>app.module.ts</code>.</li>
        <li>Edge: add <code>supabase/functions/&lt;feature&gt;/index.ts</code> and set <code>verify_jwt</code> in <code>supabase/config.toml</code>.</li>
        <li>DB: add timestamped migration SQL file.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>7. Diagram View</h2>
      <h3>Module Dependency Diagram</h3>
      <div class="mermaid">
graph TD
  Browser --> NextMiddleware[middleware.ts]
  NextMiddleware --> CatchAll[app/[[...slug]]/page.tsx]
  CatchAll --> LegacyClient[src/next/LegacyAppClient.tsx]
  LegacyClient --> App[src/App.tsx]

  App --> AuthProvider[src/hooks/useAuth.tsx]
  App --> ProtectedRoute[src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx]
  App --> SuperAdminUI[src/views/SuperAdminDashboard.tsx]
  App --> SupabaseClient[src/integrations/supabase/client.ts]

  SuperAdminUI --> InvokeAPI[src/utils/invokeProtectedApi.ts]
  InvokeAPI --> NestAPI[apps/api Nest API]

  NestAPI --> JwtGuard[JwtGuard]
  NestAPI --> RolesGuard[RolesGuard]
  NestAPI --> SuperAdminController[PlatformSuperAdminController]
  SuperAdminController --> SuperAdminService[PlatformSuperAdminService]
  SuperAdminService --> PlatformDb[PlatformDbService]
  PlatformDb --> Postgres[(Supabase Postgres)]

  App --> InvokeFn[src/utils/invokeProtectedFunction.ts]
  InvokeFn --> EdgeFns[supabase/functions/*]
  EdgeFns --> Postgres
  EdgeFns --> Stripe[Stripe/Courier APIs]
      </div>

      <h3>Data Flow Diagram</h3>
      <div class="mermaid">
flowchart LR
  U[User Input/UI] --> RQ[React Query Hooks]
  RQ --> S1[Supabase SDK direct table/RPC calls]
  RQ --> S2[invokeProtectedApi -> Nest API]
  RQ --> S3[invokeProtectedFunction -> Edge Functions]
  S1 --> DB[(Supabase Postgres + RLS)]
  S2 --> G[JWT + Role Guards]
  G --> DB
  S3 --> DB
  S3 --> EXT[External services: Stripe/Courier]
  DB --> S1
  DB --> S2
  DB --> S3
  EXT --> S3
  S1 --> UI[UI State Render]
  S2 --> UI
  S3 --> UI
      </div>

      <h3>Lifecycle Sequence Diagram (Typical /super-admin?tab=tenants)</h3>
      <div class="mermaid">
sequenceDiagram
  participant B as Browser
  participant M as Next Middleware
  participant C as React Client
  participant A as Nest API
  participant D as Platform DB

  B->>M: GET /super-admin?tab=tenants
  M-->>B: allow/redirect based on bridge cookies
  B->>C: render App + ProtectedRoute
  C->>C: useAuth/useUserRole resolve session+role
  C->>A: GET /api/platform/super-admin/tenants (Bearer token)
  A->>A: JwtGuard verify token
  A->>A: RolesGuard verify superadmin
  A->>D: SQL tenant metrics query
  D-->>A: rows
  A-->>C: JSON tenants data
  C-->>B: render tenants table
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script type="module">
    import mermaid from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@11/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs";
    mermaid.initialize({ startOnLoad: true, theme: "default", securityLevel: "loose" });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
